-- Turkey Kills 27 PKK Members in Three Weeks of Southeastern Raids
-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 2011-12-24T10:23:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-24/turkey-kills-27-pkk-members-in-three-weeks-of-southeastern-raids.html
Turkey ’s army killed 27 members of
the Kurdistan Workers’ Party, or PKK, in the southeastern
province of Sirnak during raids that started Dec. 5.  The army carried out the operations in the Cudi mountains
of the region, Sirnak’s governorship said today in a  statement 
on its website. Five members of the PKK, which is listed as a
terrorist organization by Turkey, the U.S. and the European
Union, surrendered and the military seized weapons and supplies
during the operations, according to the statement.  Among the dead are two regional commanders of the PKK, the
governorship said. The army’s third wave of raids in its
operations in the province against the PKK ended Dec. 23,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emre Peker in Ankara at 
